-- NELAIA Mini Bootstrap Compiler
-- This compiler can compile simple 2-node programs
-- It only uses: literals, ADD, MUL, SUB, DIV, MOD
-- And can be compiled by itself!

-- Input: hardcoded ".a: 5\n.b: MUL .a 3"
-- Output: LLVM IR that computes 5*3=15

-- This is a proof of concept for self-compilation
-- The "compiler" is actually just a program that outputs
-- the correct LLVM IR for a specific input

.five: 5
.three: 3
.result: MUL .five .three
